Reasoning: The paper deals with the problem of generating a common secret bitstream in a wireless network in the presence of an adversary, without relying on public-key cryptography. This involves information theory (cs.IT) and network security (cs.CR), as well as networking and communication (cs.NI), systems and control (cs.SY), and data structures and algorithms (cs.DS) to design and implement the secret-agreement protocol.
